    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1501"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1501">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/395.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The currency-plan and supplementary-loan bill, with the canal feature cut out,
                    was passed yesterday by the Assembly, which ratified that action today.</p>
                <p>The bankers’ representatives now threaten not to accept the contract without
                    insertion of a first option on canal construction if this is undertaken.</p>
                <p>I strongly recommend urging bankers to accept amended contract, according to
                    their understanding with the Department as per your February 26.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Weitzel.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
